        "## 1. What is (are?) data?\n",
        "\n",
        "A working definition: **data is information recorded through observation or measurement.** That is deliberately broad, because data has taken wildly different physical forms across history:\n",
        "\n",
        "- tally marks carved on bone,\n",
        "- London parish death records,\n",
        "- readings streamed from a wearable fitness device,\n",
        "- every post on a social media platform.\n",
        "\n",
        "*(Aside: whether \"data\" is singular or plural is genuinely contested. We will not settle it today.)*"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "id": "9c6313e3",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "9c6313e3"
      },
      "source": [
        "### Activity 1 - Data Sources (Think-Pair-Share)\n",
        "\n",
        "Name one source of data that did **not** exist 30 years ago, and one that has existed for centuries. For each, what is being *observed or measured*? Keep your two examples; we return to them when we discuss big data."
      ]
