   "metadata": {
    "id": "16962323-e9b7-42a2-8a4c-3f5a625d4d46"
   },
   "source": [
    "# \"Inference to the Best Explanation” method [Bartelborth, 2017]\n",
    "\n",
    "- Observation: Start by observing phenomena. This is your raw data. (in the detectives picture: gather clues)\n",
    "- Hypothesis Formulation: Develop potential hypotheses that might explain the observed data.\n",
    "- Refinement: Some theories might not fit the facts. So, they’re discarded.\n",
    "- Comparison: Which of our remaining theories best explains the data?\n",
    "- Selection: Choose the hypothesis (or hypotheses) that offers the most plausible and comprehensive explanation in line with other established knowledge."
   ]
  },
